public class HandoverRequestRecord
extends Record

Handover Request Record

The Handover Request Record identifies a list of possible alternative carriers that the Handover Requester device would be able to use for further communication with the Handover Selector. At least a single alternative carrier MUST be specified by the Handover Requester. If multiple alternative carriers are specified, the Handover Selector SHOULD process the records in order and acknowledge the first appropriate match, if any. Only Alternative Carrier Records or Collision Resolution Records have a defined meaning in the payload of a Handover Request Record. However, an implementation SHALL silently ignore and SHALL NOT raise an error if it encounters other unknown record types.

Author:
Thomas Rorvik Skjolberg (skjolber@gmail.com)
